The paper focuses on improving network quality-of-service (QoS) measurement and network resource allocation in smart homes, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed encrypted packet classification scheme also involves security and privacy concerns, which could be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a deep learning-based classification scheme, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also involves software-defined network technology, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE).
